How to Use Claude Skills

  The /generate-blog and /optimize-email commands are Claude Code slash commands that you type directly in this conversation. Here's how they work:

  Blog Generation

  Research topics first:
  /generate-blog --research
  This runs the blog research mode to analyze trends and suggest topics.

  Generate a specific post:
  /generate-blog "How AI is Transforming Network Marketing in 2026"
  This generates a blog post with the given title in all 4 languages.

  Full automation:
  /generate-blog --full-auto
  This researches, generates, deploys, and sends notification email.

  Email Optimization

  Check all campaigns:
  /optimize-email --all
  This shows status of all 9 email campaigns (sent/remaining counts).

  Check specific campaign:
  /optimize-email bfh
  This analyzes the BFH campaign specifically.

  Deliverability check:
  /optimize-email --deliverability
  This reviews spam monitor status and bounce rates.

  MCP Servers (Automatic)

  The MCP servers I configured (Firestore, GA4) load automatically when Claude Code starts. You don't invoke them directly - they enable me to query your database and analytics directly when needed.

  Example queries I can now do:
  - "How many BFH contacts haven't been sent yet?"
  - "What's the click rate from email traffic this week?"
  - "Show me the current batch sizes for all campaigns"